
1. IN the app folder (eg: dashboard), I created "templates" folder. 
2.In "templates" folder, I put the html page to be used (here, Insurance_compare.html)

3. In the django-app folder(eg: dashboard),in the views.py:
  use the render and request commands to point to the html page.

4. In the same django-app folder, in urls.py:
    use the 'path' command to assign the url 

5. Also, update the django-app folder in the django-project folder (here: mysite): 
       use the 'path' command to assign the url

6. THen run the command: ( python manage.py runserver ) in the project folder.

 
Eg:url link in https://youtu.be/6WpAZmTsJXI

